        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 5:54PM EDT by NWS Indianapolis IN</headline>
        <description>At 553 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Crawfordsville, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Crawfordsville, Lebanon, Zionsville, Whitestown, Thorntown, Ladoga,
Jamestown, Darlington, New Market, Advance, New Ross, and Ulen.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 65 between mile markers 129 and 147.
Interstate 74 between mile markers 32 and 54.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
